dt: {bc}a graphic symbol of Chinese origin that has the form of a circle divided evenly into two symmetrical teardrop shapes representing {d_link|yin|yin} and {d_link|yang|yang}
One of the teardrop shapes in a yin-yang symbol is dark (usually black) and the other is light (usually white), with each containing a small circle of the other color.

shortdef: a graphic symbol of Chinese origin that has the form of a circle divided evenly into two symmetrical teardrop shapes representing yin and yang
